CPAM-TWW

CPAM(Cross-Platform Application Management) is an area focus on making management of application easier across different OS platforms. 

The Written Word Inc. has a exact toolset written in Python for this purpose.

The toolsets consist of three tools for software building, software packaging and package utility for package installation and  removal. 


This an effort to implement TWW toolsets using Perl lanauage. 


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc CPAM::TWW

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=CPAM-TWW

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/CPAM-TWW

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/CPAM-TWW

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/CPAM-TWW/


